  "subject": "Make stand-alone Policy environment",
  "commit_message": "Make stand-alone Policy environment\n\nThis is a first cut at making it possible to easily run Policy\ncomponents within a stand-alone environment.  Made the following\nchanges:\n- enhanced wait_for_port.sh to accept a list of hosts/ports\n- enhanced wait_for_port.sh to accept an optional command to execute\n  when the wait completes\n- removed \"extra\" services from the drools-apps yml so that the entire\n  thing can be brought up in a single invocation\n- modified the drools-apps setup.sh\n\nWith these changes, a developer can clone the csit repo, modify\nthe docker image versions in the yml file, and then bring up the\ncomponents using:\n\n  docker-compose -f scripts/policy/drools-apps/docker-compose-drools-apps.yml\n    up --detach\n\nNote: this does not preload or deploy any policies; that must be done\nmanually via curl.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-2742\nChange-Id: I98b1fb2fcc00c2cc5edbdc3ecf87cb213673fb18\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
